<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Item&nbsp;8.01.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Other Events. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On August&nbsp;19, 2010,
Intel Corporation (&#147;Intel&#148;) announced that it had entered into a definitive agreement to acquire McAfee, Inc. (&#147;McAfee&#148;). Intel and McAfee held a joint investor conference call on August&nbsp;19, 2010, to discuss the execution of
the definitive agreement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A transcript of the conference call, as well as copies of the materials referenced during the conference call, are
attached as Exhibits 99.1 and 99.2 and are incorporated by reference herein. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Additionally, on August&nbsp;19, 2010, Intel made available on
its website an internal management presentation regarding the proposed transaction. A transcript of the presentation is attached as Exhibit 99.3 and incorporated by reference herein. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:2%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Additional information and where to find it </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McAfee intends to file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;) a preliminary proxy statement and a definitive proxy statement
and other relevant materials in connection with the merger. The definitive proxy statement will be sent or given to the stockholders of McAfee. Before making any voting or investment decision with respect to the merger, investors and stockholders of
McAfee are urged to read the proxy statement and the other relevant materials when they become available because they will contain important information about the merger. The proxy statement and other relevant materials (when they become available),
and any other documents filed by McAfee with the SEC, may be obtained free of charge at the SEC&#146;s website at www.sec.gov, at McAfee&#146;s website at www.McAfee.com (click on &#147;Investor Information&#148;, then on &#147;SEC Filings&#148;),
or from McAfee by contacting Investor Relations by mail at McAfee, Inc., 3965 Freedom Circle, Santa Clara, California 95054, Attention: Investor Relations, or by telephone at (408)&nbsp;346-5223. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:2%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Participants in the Solicitation </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McAfee and Intel and their respective directors and executive officers may be deemed to be participants in the solicitation of proxies from McAfee
stockholders in connection with the merger. Information about Intel&#146;s directors and executive officers is set forth in Intel&#146;s 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the SEC on April&nbsp;2, 2010 and its Annual Report on Form 10-K
for the year ended December&nbsp;26, 2009, filed on February&nbsp;22, 2010, respectively. Information about McAfee&#146;s directors and executive officers is set forth in its 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the SEC on April&nbsp;30,
2010 (as revised on May&nbsp;10, 2010). Additional information regarding the interests of participants in the solicitation of proxies in connection with the merger will be included in the definitive proxy statement that McAfee intends to file with
the SEC. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:2%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Forward-Looking Statements </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This Form 8-K, including the exhibits filed with this Form 8-K, contain certain forward-looking statements regarding the proposed transaction between
Intel and McAfee. Actual events or results may differ materially from those contained in these forward-looking statements. Among the important factors that could cause future events or results to vary from those addressed in the forward-looking
statements include without limitation, risks and uncertainties arising from the possibility that the closing of the transaction may be delayed or may not occur; difficulties with the integration process or the realization of the benefits of the
transaction; general economic conditions in the regions and industries in which Intel and McAfee operate; and litigation or regulatory matters involving antitrust and other issues that could affect the closing of the transaction. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In addition, please refer to the documents that Intel files with the SEC on Forms 10-K, 10-Q and 8-K. The filings by Intel identify and address other
important factors that could cause events and results to differ materially from those contained in the forward-looking statements set forth in this Form 8-K and in Intel&#146;s other filings. Intel is under no duty to update any of the
forward-looking statements after the date of this Form 8-K to conform to actual results. </FONT></P>

<DESCRIPTION>TRANSCRIPT OF INTEL CORPORATION AND MCAFEE, INC
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Transcript of Intel Corporation and McAfee, Inc</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Additional information and where to find it </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McAfee intends to file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;) a preliminary proxy statement and a definitive proxy statement
and other relevant materials in connection with the merger. The definitive proxy statement will be sent or given to the stockholders of McAfee. Before making any voting or investment decision with respect to the merger, investors and stockholders of
McAfee are urged to read the proxy statement and the other relevant materials when they become available because they will contain important information about the merger. The proxy statement and other relevant materials (when they become available),
and any other documents filed by McAfee with the SEC, may be obtained free of charge at the SEC&#146;s website at www.sec.gov, at McAfee&#146;s website at www.McAfee.com (click on &#147;Investor Information&#148;, then on &#147;SEC Filings&#148;),
or from McAfee by contacting Investor Relations by mail at McAfee, Inc., 3965 Freedom Circle, Santa Clara, California 95054, Attention: Investor Relations, or by telephone at (408)&nbsp;346-5223. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Participants in the Solicitation </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McAfee
and Intel and their respective directors and executive officers may be deemed to be participants in the solicitation of proxies from McAfee stockholders in connection with the merger. Information about Intel&#146;s directors and executive officers
is set forth in Intel&#146;s 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the SEC on April&nbsp;2, 2010 and its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;26, 2009, filed on February&nbsp;22, 2010, respectively. Information about
McAfee&#146;s directors and executive officers is set forth in its 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the SEC on April&nbsp;30, 2010 (as revised on May&nbsp;10, 2010). Additional information regarding the interests of participants in
the solicitation of proxies in connection with the merger will be included in the definitive proxy statement that McAfee intends to file with the SEC. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;* </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Aug 19, 2010 / 02:00PM GMT, MFE - McAfee, Inc. to be acquired by Intel Corporation - Webcast</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Kevin Sellers </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Intel Corporation - VP-IR </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Paul
Otellini </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Intel Corporation - President&nbsp;&amp; CEO </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Renee James </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Intel Corporation -
SVP&nbsp;&amp; GM Software and Services Group </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>David DeWalt </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>McAfee, Inc. - President&nbsp;&amp; CEO </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Andy Bryant </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Intel Corporation - EVP,
Chief Administrative Officer </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>CONFERENCE CALL PARTICIPANTS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Jim Covello </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Goldman Sachs - Analyst
</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Uche Orji </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>UBS -
Analyst </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Stacy Rasgon </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Sanford Bernstein - Analyst </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>John
Pitzer </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Credit Suisse - Analyst </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Ross Seymore </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Deutsche Bank - Analyst
</I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>John Barton </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Cowen
and Company - Analyst </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Mark Lipacis </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Morgan Stanley - Analyst </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>PRESENTATION </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operator </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Good morning, ladies and gentlemen, thank you for standing by. Welcome to today&#146;s conference call to discuss Intel&#146;s acquisition of McAfee. All
lines have been placed on mute to prevent any background noise. After the speakers&#146; remarks there will be a question-and-answer session. (Operator instructions) I would now like to turn the presentation over to your host for today&#146;s call,
Mr.&nbsp;Kevin Sellers, Vice President of Investor Relations. Please proceed, sir. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Kevin Sellers - </B><B><I>Intel Corporation -
VP-IR</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Good morning and welcome, everyone, to our conference call regarding the announcement of Intel&#146;s pending acquisition
of McAfee Inc. I&#146;m joined today by Paul Otellini, President and CEO of Intel; Andy Bryant, Executive Vice President and Chief Administration Officer of Intel; Renee James, Senior Vice President and General Manager of the Software and Solutions
Group at Intel; and we&#146;re also joined today by Dave DeWalt, President and CEO of McAfee, Inc. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We excuse our CFO, Stacy Smith, who is
currently on a well-earned sabbatical for several weeks. Stacy will be back in a few weeks and will resume his place next to Paul at our next earnings conference call, scheduled for October&nbsp;12, 2010. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Today&#146;s conference call is being delivered via audio conference and webcast. Those joining by webcast will note that there are slides that will be
accompanying this conference call. Those dialed into the audio bridge may wish to log into the webcast so you can follow the slides linked to the speaker comments. This conference call is being recorded and will be available for replay on our
website in approximately two hours after the conclusion of this call. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">3 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>F<SMALL>INAL</SMALL> T<SMALL>RANSCRIPT</SMALL> </B></FONT></P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Aug 19, 2010 / 02:00PM GMT, MFE - McAfee, Inc. to be acquired by Intel Corporation - Webcast</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A few important items before I begin &#151; let me remind everyone that today&#146;s discussion does
contain forward-looking statements based on the environment as we currently see it and, as such, does include risks and uncertainties. We assume no obligation to update these forward-looking statements. Please refer to our press release and our most
recent 10-Q filings of Intel and McAfee for more information on the specific risk factors that could cause actual results to differ materially. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Our agenda today will proceed as follows. Paul Otellini will provide some strategic overview about this transaction and why Intel has made this
investment. He will be followed by Renee James, who will provide some more details about the security business segment and how this acquisition will bring new innovations in security to computing. Then, Dave DeWalt, CEO of McAfee, will have a few
comments about McAfee&#146;s perspective on this acquisition. Finally, Andy Bryant will provide a summary of the financial details of this transaction. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">With that, let me now hand it over to Paul. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Paul Otellini - </B><B><I>Intel Corporation -
President&nbsp;&amp; CEO</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Thanks, Kevin. I&#146;m pleased to announce today the planned acquisition of McAfee Corporation by
Intel. This is an important strategic step that we believe will benefit Intel, our stockholders, our customers and Internet users worldwide. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Before I get into the strategic reasoning behind the acquisition, let me first review the specifics of the deal. It&#146;s a $7.68 billion all-cash
transaction. It has unanimous approval by both boards. McAfee will be maintained as a wholly-owned subsidiary of Intel Corporation. We have a commitment by the McAfee management team to stay on for multiple years post-close, and Intel is giving its
commitment to the McAfee brand and all McAfee product offerings. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Now let me talk about why this deal is important and makes strategic sense
for Intel. Over the past couple of decades, there have been a few critically important inflections in the computing landscape. In the 1990s, as the Internet began to grow, we added capabilities to our platforms so that users could connect to the
Internet and with each other in ways that were previously not possible. PC demand exploded as a result. In the last decade the combination of wireless connectivity and energy-efficient performance in computing platforms drove a new wave of growth in
mobile computing that continues to accelerate across a wider and wider array of computing devices. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Today I believe that we are entering a new
era for computing platforms that has brought strategic implications for our Company and will impact users worldwide. We now live in a world of billions of connected computing devices. Internet traffic is growing at a 40%&nbsp;per year compounded
annual growth rate. Most of us are spending more and more of our lives online for productivity, entertainment, social networking or e-commerce related activities. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Growing alongside the increasing Internet usage is the sophistication and frequency of security attacks against individual consumers, enterprises and
governments around the world. The number of new security threats identified every month continues to rise, and in the first half of this year alone there were over 10&nbsp;million new malware variants added to the McAfee threat database. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As a result, we have concluded that security has now become the third pillar of computing, joining energy-efficient performance and Internet conductivity
in importance. We believe that the future of computing will rest on improvements in and the integration of these three key pillars. We believe that security will be most effective when enabled in hardware. Joining the assets of McAfee with Intel
will accelerate and enhance the combination of hardware and software solutions, improving the overall security of our platforms. Bringing together McAfee and Intel will facilitate innovative breakthroughs in security going forward. The bottom line
is this will better protect Internet users and their devices, and that will accelerate growth for Intel and value for our shareholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In
summary, we are very excited about this transaction, as it allows Intel to innovate across all three key pillars of computing: energy efficient performance, Internet connectivity and now security. As part of Intel&#146;s transformation from a PC
company into a computing company, the addition of this capability positions Intel well for the future of computing across a broad range of devices and usages. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">With that, let me hand the call over to Renee James, who runs our software and services group, for more details about this acquisition. Renee?
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">4 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>F<SMALL>INAL</SMALL> T<SMALL>RANSCRIPT</SMALL> </B></FONT></P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Aug 19, 2010 / 02:00PM GMT, MFE - McAfee, Inc. to be acquired by Intel Corporation - Webcast</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>Renee James</B><B><I> - Intel Corporation - SVP&nbsp;&amp; GM Software and Services Group </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Many of you may not be aware that Intel has been collaborating closely with McAfee for over 18 months on ways to improve security. We know, trust and
respect each other. They have phenomenally talented employees, and after working alongside each other and recognizing that we share a common vision for improving security, it made good sense that we take this step. The threats and opportunities are
simply too large and important to tackle alone, and that&#146;s why we&#146;re here today. The proposed acquisition of McAfee executes against Intel&#146;s software strategy to grow our business by using software to enhance hardware. We&#146;ve done
this successfully with over a dozen software acquisitions, including Wind River and Havok, which represents a fundamental belief that the most pressing problems in computing will require both hardware and software solutions. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As Paul said, security is top of mind for consumers, and knowing that your PC, your smart phone or your Internet-connected device is securely connected
to the network and to the world can change how useful that device really is. This is especially true in mobile devices, ones that are connected to the cloud that do not have the capacity to hold all of the storage &#151; all of the information in
storage and memory, but will always be connected. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The McAfee transaction is a logical next step in security. As you may know, our active
management technology and our vPro family of platforms have programmable defense filters that systematically guard against viruses and malicious attacks today. We also recently launched the Intel anti-theft technology, which will disable a computer
if it&#146;s lost or stolen. Our teams have been working together to build enhanced security solutions that can better protect consumers and the industry from malicious events. Through this partnership we&#146;ve had an opportunity to learn about
McAfee, the possibilities of what a closer partnership between hardware and software could bring and their incredible employees. I&#146;m excited to say that the first fruits of our strategic partnership will be released in the early part of 2011.
We look forward to having McAfee join the Intel family. As a subsidiary, McAfee will continue to focus on its current, very profitable business. It will also maintain all of its current product lines and support for multiple architectures and
platforms. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">And with that I&#146;d like to turn it over to Dave. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>David DeWalt</B><B><I> - McAfee, Inc. - President&nbsp;&amp; CEO </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Okay, thank you, Paul; thank you, Renee. I&#146;m very pleased to be here this morning. For those of you I don&#146;t know personally, I&#146;m the
President and CEO of McAfee. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Today is a great day for McAfee&#146;s employees, customers and stockholders. Over the last several years,
McAfee has been on a tremendous journey to make the world a safer place. Through our focused strategy and execution, we have effectively emerged as a leading global Internet security provider. McAfee&#146;s products are used by over 200&nbsp;million
users worldwide, and we have an incredibly strong partner ecosystem. Unlike any other security provider, McAfee offers a whole complement of consumer and corporate security products, services and solutions covering endpoint security, network
security and cloud security with the most comprehensive global threat intelligence in the industry, with cloud services such as Web, content and application reputation. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">By becoming part of the Intel organization, we believe we can continue to create new and innovative security solutions. As Paul and Renee have outlined,
with the explosion of new IP-connected devices and continued growth in the threat landscape, our opportunity has expanded dramatically and our strategy is paying off. What I hope you hear is the similarities of the vision we share with Intel.
I&#146;m very excited and fully committed to joining the Intel team in continuing to lead the McAfee organization as an independent subsidiary. I want to thank McAfee&#146;s employees, our partners and our customers, and look forward to the next
chapter in our relationship with Intel. Looking ahead, I truly believe the future is bright for McAfee. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>Kevin Sellers</B><B><I> - Intel
Corporation - VP-IR </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Okay, thanks, Dave. We&#146;ll end the prepared remarks section with a few comments on the transaction itself from
Andy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>Andy Bryant</B><B><I> - Intel Corporation - EVP, Chief Administrative Officer </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Good morning. I will briefly review some of the terms and operational aspects of the transaction. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">5 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>F<SMALL>INAL</SMALL> T<SMALL>RANSCRIPT</SMALL> </B></FONT></P>

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8px; padding-right:8px"> <P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Aug 19, 2010 / 02:00PM GMT, MFE - McAfee, Inc. to be acquired by Intel Corporation - Webcast</B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:3px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:1px">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As Paul said, Intel has agreed to purchase all the common shares of McAfee at $48 per share in an
all-cash transaction. The purchase price is approximately $7.7 billion. Net of cash, the purchase price is $6.8 billion. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On a GAAP basis we
expect the combination to be slightly dilutive to earnings in the first year of operations and approximately flat in the second year. GAAP purchase accounting requires us to take a one-time write-down of deferred revenue when the transaction closes
and to amortize acquired intangibles. On a non-GAAP basis, excluding these two adjustments, we expect the combination to be slightly accretive in the first year and to improve beyond that. Longer term, we expect the financial and strategic synergies
from this combination to be significant. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The purchase price of $48 per share includes a premium of approximately 50% over the closing price
of the stock yesterday and four weeks ago. The premium is within the range of recent large software and securities transactions, and we believe it is a reasonable price for McAfee&#146;s growth and profitability and for the potential additional
value McAfee and Intel can bring together. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The multiple of price to earnings, based on analysts&#146; forecast for 2011, is also in line with
recent technology deals. Intel&#146;s and McAfee&#146;s Boards of Directors have unanimously approved this transaction, which we hope may close as early as the end of this year, subject to regulatory approvals, McAfee stockholder approval and other
customary closing conditions specified in the agreement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In summary, the initial impact of this transaction will be to reduce cash on the
balance sheet. In the first year or two, we expect the impact of income statement to be largely neutral. Over time we expect the full benefit to owners, customers and consumers to be substantial as Intel and McAfee combine resources to take security
to a new level. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>Kevin Sellers</B><B><I> - Intel Corporation - VP-IR </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Thanks, Andy. We&#146;ll now move to Q&amp;A. We&#146;d like to have each participant ask just one question and if you have a follow-up, you can follow up
with one, and then we&#146;ll move to the next questioner. So Carrie, you can introduce our first question. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>QUESTION AND ANSWER

<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operator </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">(Operator instructions) Jim
Covello, Goldman Sachs. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>Jim Covello</B><B><I> - Goldman Sachs - Analyst </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Great, guys, thanks so much for taking the question, congratulations on the announcement of the deal today. I guess maybe if I could ask the first
question, how much of the strategic focus of this deal, looking forward, is going to be in the embedded market as opposed to the traditional core PC market on either the consumer or enterprise side? </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">We think that there&#146;s an explosive growth opportunity in the embedded, and by embedded, we include into that traditional embedded devices as well as
new, emerging categories like Internet-connected TVs and other markets that we can serve and reach with Atom. Dave, do you want to add anything to that? </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>David DeWalt</B><B><I> - McAfee,

of the new Internet protocols, we are seeing an explosion of billions of devices on the Internet. Those devices need to be secured, and with the threat landscape, combination with those devices, the embedded market is a very specific and
high-opportunity market for us. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

Corporation - President&nbsp;&amp; CEO </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Sure, that&#146;s a good question, Uche. In working with them, the notion of moving beyond just

those kinds of projects, we began to understand two things &#151; one, that having a deeper collaboration, where we could look long term and try to look at the combination, the deeply-integrated combination of hardware and software capabilities,
would add substantial value to our platforms and differentiation to our platforms, number one. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Number two, it became pretty clear to us that

doing for years and years and years, which is making the product offering and platform an improved product. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">So yes, I think it will do &#151;
it will help protect and enhance and differentiate our product in the future. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Stacy Rasgon - </B><B><I>Sanford Bernstein -
Analyst</I></B><B> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">And if I could have one more follow-up, if you are talking about selling these things together, whether it&#146;s price
bundles or anything else, given the recent difficulty that you&#146;ve had with the FTC and the DoJ and everything else, are there any regulatory issues that we ought to be watching for as you start to bring more of this co-selling of hardware and
security software together? </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Well, of course, this is subject to regulatory approval, as Andy said in his comments or Kevin said, as well. I don&#146;t know that we&#146;re looking at
bundling, per se. Right now we are looking at &#151; and by the way, I will say, we intend to continue to work with other security vendors, so this is not a McAfee-only kind of strategy. What we think we can do, though, is by having McAfee in the
Intel family, we can have a deeper integration and overall, probably, the best capability that&#146;s possible to offer. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I></I></B><B>Kevin Sellers</B><B><I> - Intel Corporation - VP-IR </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Carrie, that&#146;s it, you can wrap it up for us. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:1px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Operator </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Thank you. That does conclude today&#146;s teleconference. You may now disconnect. </FONT></P>

<div style='position:absolute;left:64px;top:188px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>McAfee intends to file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the
&#147;SEC&#148;) a preliminary proxy </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:206px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>statement and a definitive proxy
statement and other relevant materials in connection with the merger. The </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:224px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>definitive proxy statement will be sent or given to the stockholders of McAfee.
Before making any voting or </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:242px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>investment decision with respect to the merger,
investors and stockholders of McAfee are urged to read </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:260px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>the proxy statement
and the other relevant materials when they become available because they will </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:277px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>contain important information about the merger. The proxy statement and other
relevant materials (when </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:295px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>they become available), and any other documents
filed by McAfee with the SEC, may be obtained free of </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:313px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>charge at the
SEC&#146;s</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:227px;top:313px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>website, at www.sec.gov, at McAfee&#146;s website at www.
mcafee</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:749px;top:313px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>.com (click on </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:331px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>&#147;Investor Information&#148;, then on &#147;SEC Filings&#148;) or from McAfee
by contacting Investor Relations by mail at </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:349px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>McAfee , Inc., 3965 Freedom
Circle, Santa Clara, California 95054, Attention: Investor Relations, by </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:367px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>telephone at 408 346&#45;5223.</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:64px;top:416px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>Participants in the Solicitation</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:64px;top:440px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>McAfee and Intel and their respective directors and executive officers may be
deemed to be participants </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:458px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>in the solicitation of proxies from McAfee
stockholders in connection with the merger. Information about </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:476px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>Intel&#146;s
directors and executive officers is set forth in Intel&#146;s 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:494px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>with the SEC on April 2, 2010 and its Annual Report on Form 10&#45;K for the year
ended December 26, 2009, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:511px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>filed on February 22, 2010, respectively.
Information about McAfee&#146;s directors and executive officers is set </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:55px;top:529px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>forth</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:97px;top:529px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>in</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:116px;top:529px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>its</div>

<DOCUMENT>
<TYPE>EX-99.3
<SEQUENCE>4
<FILENAME>dex993.htm
<DESCRIPTION>MANAGEMENT PRESENTATION, DATED AUGUST 18, 2010
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Management Presentation, dated August 18, 2010</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.3 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Additional information and where to find it </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McAfee intends to file with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the &#147;SEC&#148;) a preliminary proxy statement and a definitive proxy statement
and other relevant materials in connection with the merger. The definitive proxy statement will be sent or given to the stockholders of McAfee. Before making any voting or investment decision with respect to the merger, investors and stockholders of
McAfee are urged to read the proxy statement and the other relevant materials when they become available because they will contain important information about the merger. The proxy statement and other relevant materials (when they become available),
and any other documents filed by McAfee with the SEC, may be obtained free of charge at the SEC&#146;s website at <U>www.sec.gov</U>, at McAfee&#146;s website at <U>www.McAfee.com</U> (click on &#147;Investor Information&#148;, then on &#147;SEC
Filings&#148;), or from McAfee by contacting Investor Relations by mail at McAfee, Inc., 3965 Freedom Circle, Santa Clara, California 95054, Attention: Investor Relations, or by telephone at (408)&nbsp;346-5223. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Participants in the Solicitation </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">McAfee
and Intel and their respective directors and executive officers may be deemed to be participants in the solicitation of proxies from McAfee stockholders in connection with the merger. Information about Intel&#146;s directors and executive officers
is set forth in Intel&#146;s 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the SEC on April&nbsp;2, 2010 and its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;26, 2009, filed on February&nbsp;22, 2010, respectively. Information about
McAfee&#146;s directors and executive officers is set forth in its 2010 proxy statement on Schedule 14A filed with the SEC on April&nbsp;30, 2010 (as revised on May&nbsp;10, 2010). Additional information regarding the interests of participants in
the solicitation of proxies in connection with the merger will be included in the definitive proxy statement that McAfee intends to file with the SEC. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;* </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Transcript of Management Presentation </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>August&nbsp;18, 2010 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Bill: </B>Thanks
for joining us. I&#146;m Bill Kircos with Intel Corporation and today the company announced the acquisition of McAfee at 7.68 billion dollars. I&#146;m fortunate enough to have the top brass with me today. Renee James, senior vice president of the
software and services group and Dave DeWalt, CEO of McAfee. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Renee, let me start with you. What excites you about this deal? </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Renee: </B>Well, I am first of all very excited about what we can do together. As the world of connected computing continues to grow, we are adding
security as one of the major focus areas for Intel, along with power and performance. We&#146;re going to add a new &#147;P&#148; &#150; Protection. And we&#146;re very excited about the combination and innovation in security that we can make
between the two companies. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Bill: </B>Great answer. So why specifically McAfee then? </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Renee: </B>That&#146;s a great question. We have been partners with McAfee for a long time; we&#146;re a customer. And we&#146;ve got a lot of
experience working with Dave and his team. We&#146;re very excited about the current product line, and some of their efforts in R&amp;D. Just amazing people. And we think that combination with our leadership products is a really powerful thing that
we can do together. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Bill: </B>Dave, what gets you jazzed up about this and why Intel? </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Dave: </B>Well one of the things that Renee said too but first the reputation of Intel is legendary. I mean I find the innovation, the research, the
development, the commitment over the years &#150; it&#146;s fabulous. And for McAfee, we&#146;re pleased to be a part of that. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">What you said
as well. Connected devices are exploding. As the movement of the new internet from IPV4 to IPV6 changes, we&#146;re going to trillions of devices over time. And security is really important as a part of that. So we share a similar vision and we
share innovation. And it&#146;s exciting &#150; it&#146;s truly exciting. And, we&#146;re also neighbors in many locations as well. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Renee:
</B>Right &#150; that&#146;s what we found out. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Bill: </B>Renee, talk to me about how security fits into our traditional business as we
have a really fast growing PC business but also our growth ambitions in the mobile wireless area. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Renee: </B>Security, as I said in my
first comments, security is really important across our existing businesses both in the data center and the connection through the network through the data center and cloud as well as obviously in your PC today. As the PC market continues to expand,
continues to be a great business, security is increasingly a consideration for all users. As we&#146;ve been talking about and have made other software acquisitions are our growth businesses around mobile devices, imbedded devices and consumer
electronics. All those billions of devices are going to be connected to the internet and all of them are going to need security. So we think that the technology of McAfee is applicable across all of the segments that we serve and that people use
computing. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Bill: </B>Great. Dave, I&#146;m sure people are going to ask: Are you going to stick around? And what does this deal mean to
your customers? </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Dave: </B>Oh I tell you, I can&#146;t be more pleased with this whole thing. It&#146;s almost like it&#146;s a dream come
true in some ways that we have a chance to fulfill our vision and our strategy. And of course I&#146;m sticking around. I&#146;m very excited about that. I&#146;ll be here for a long time with Intel and I&#146;m excited about the future of the
company and excited about the future opportunity for us with security and innovation. As I said before so looking forward to it. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Dave:
</B>Last question for you Renee. What are your plans for McAfee in terms of how you&#146;ll structure it and any message for the employees out there? </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Renee: </B>Yes. We are going to keep McAfee as a wholly owned subsidiary like we did with Wind River, which we acquired last year, and several other
acquisitions that we&#146;ve made. And we expect, as Dave just told you, that Dave and leadership team and the entire employee base will be staying with us and continuing to build great products and innovate new products as part of the Intel family.
</FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Dave: </B>I think that&#146;s what&#146;s important to add on there is that the employees are valued
here. That&#146;s what&#146;s exciting. That&#146;s Intel&#146;s culture, that&#146;s our culture, so all employees are welcome to be a part of this and I think from customers and from partners of ours, Intel has always treated them as the highest
priority and we&#146;ll be doing the same thing and, of course, innovating even more. So very exciting times for us all I think. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Bill:
</B>Terrific. Thanks and congratulations again. </FONT></P>
</BODY></HTML>
</TEXT>
</DOCUMENT>
